 Educational Background



 


London School of Economics and Political Science

                  LSE was founded in 1895 and has grown to become one of the foremost social science universities in the world, ranked alongside Harvard, UC Berkeley and Stanford. 

A specialist university with an international intake, LSE's reach extends from its central London campus to around the world. 

    The School has a cosmopolitan student body, with around 9,500 full time students from 140 countries
    It has a staff of just over 3,000, with about 46 per cent drawn from countries outside the UK
    Over 100 languages are spoken on LSE's campus
    An influential network of over 160,000 LSE alumni spans the world, covering over 190 countries with more than 80 active alumni groups.                





 Career History



Chief Financial Officer

                                    Current                


Zegona Communications Plc


                  Zegona Communications Plc operates and acquires businesses in the Europe's telecommunications, media and technology sector, focusing on network based communications and entertainment opportunities. The company operates in two segments: Telecable Group and Central Costs. The Telecable Group segment represents the activity of the Telecable business in Spain. The Central Costs segment represents costs incurred by all Zegona Group entities supporting the corporate activities of the Group. Zegona Communications was founded by Eamonn O'Hare, Howard Kalika and Robert Samuelson on January 19, 2015 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.                




Group Financial Controller

                                    Prior                


AB Mauri (UK) Ltd.


                  AB Mauri (UK) Ltd. distributes yeast and bakery ingredients. It offers stabilized cream, compressed and dried yeast; bread, micro-ingredients, sweet bakery, donut mixes and concentrates, fillings, gels, colors, flavors and regional specialty products. The company was founded in 1868 and is headquartered in Peterborough, the United Kingdom.                




Finance Director

                                    Prior                


Central European Media Enterprises Ltd.


                  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd. operates as a media and entertainment company. It operates through the following segments: Broadcast, Media Pro Entertainment and New Media. The Broadcast segment includes 36 television channels. The Media Pro Entertainment segment involves in production and distribution business. The New Media division operates online products and distribution platforms across six markets. The company was founded by Ronald Steven Lauder in June 1994 and is headquartered in Hamilton, Bermuda.                





